<collectionCode id="ED4395980941B21FEEB5FEDF230B4B34" box="[695,768,259,285]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">NMW</collectionCode>
. Plus additional 
<typeStatus id="54E9B3FF0941B21FEFBAFEDF248A4B35" box="[952,1153,258,285]" isOtherTypeStatus="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">non-type material</typeStatus>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0941B21FECC5FEFA253E4BDC" blockId="21.[151,1437,150,680]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FECC5FEFA21AA4B69" bold="true" box="[199,417,294,320]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Short description:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FEDA8FEFB22424B69" authorityName="Kirchner, Kruckenhauser, Pichler, Borkenhagen &amp; Freyhof" authorityYear="2020" box="[426,585,294,321]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shamal">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FEDA8FEFB22424B69" box="[426,585,294,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Garra shamal</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is differentiated from the other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FE82CFEFB247F4B68" box="[1070,1140,295,321]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FE82CFEFB247F4B68" box="[1070,1140,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Garra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Hajar Mountain by absence of bold-black middle caudal-fin rays with white membranes (vs. present in other species). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FE8E7FE9725884B4D" authorityName="Kirchner, Kruckenhauser, Pichler, Borkenhagen &amp; Freyhof" authorityYear="2020" box="[1253,1411,330,357]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shamal">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FE8E7FE9725884B4D" box="[1253,1411,330,357]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Garra shamal</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is further distinguished by having a strongly mottled flank pattern (vs. plain or almost plain in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FE8B2FEB325424BA1" authorityName="Krupp" authorityYear="1988" box="[1200,1353,366,393]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallagheri">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FE8B2FEB325424BA1" box="[1200,1353,366,393]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">G. gallagheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FE983FEB3211E4B85" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipinnis">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FE983FEB3211E4B85" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">G. longipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a white dorsal-fin tip (vs. not different from rest of fin in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FEF9FFE4F24384B85" authorityName="Krupp" authorityYear="1988" box="[925,1075,402,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallagheri">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FEF9FFE4F24384B85" box="[925,1075,402,429]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">G. gallagheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FE865FE4F250D4B85" box="[1127,1286,402,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipinnis">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FE865FE4F250D4B85" box="[1127,1286,402,429]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">G. longipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), orange spot at the upper opercle absent (vs. present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FEE71FE6B231A4BF9" authorityName="Fowler &amp; Steinitz" authorityYear="1956" box="[627,785,438,465]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barreimiae">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FEE71FE6B231A4BF9" box="[627,785,438,465]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">G. barreimiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), orange scales on the flank usually absent (vs. present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FEC95FE07213F4BDD" authorityName="Fowler &amp; Steinitz" authorityYear="1956" box="[151,308,474,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barreimiae">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FEC95FE07213F4BDD" box="[151,308,474,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">G. barreimiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 10–14 gill rakers on the lower limb of the first gill arch (vs. 
<quantity id="4CAAA0B80941B21FE81FFE06248B4BDD" box="[1053,1152,474,501]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.191" metricValueMax="4.572" metricValueMin="3.81" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" unit="in" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FE885FE07252F4BDD" authorityName="Fowler &amp; Steinitz" authorityYear="1956" box="[1159,1316,474,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barreimiae">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FE885FE07252F4BDD" box="[1159,1316,474,501]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">G. barreimiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
